				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Hard LDoN<a name="45715"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jun 13 04 5:34 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I tend to fade a lot in hard LDONs, but only because I don't really spend the time to scope out rooms. I just mez what I see and see how many come. 
<br />

<br />
Monks can be very useful for pulling hard LDONs. They have a lull that is unresistable, and can help break up some big rooms (they still pull much slower than bards, so you'll probably end up being the main puller, but will be able to ask for a lull if you need it). An example of this is in EC, The Halls of War, where you start out at an intersection, no room to split or anything, and usually turns into a 4 or 5 pull. I did this with a monk, just had him lull one mob, and was able to turn it into two pulls of two instead of having them all at once.
<br />

<br />
</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
