				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Hard LDoN<a name="45741"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jun 13 04 1:27 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I've found that sometimes you have to pull the hard ldon because your the only one that can. In those cases, I have employed with great success proximity agro and crowd control, don't try and single them that takes too much mana and you end up dying more likely. 
<br />
If you hit the mob with any damage or debuff he will yell out and charge you and his assist range increases. If you just get close enough to him he see's you his assist range is smaller, therefore less mobs will agro initially, then mez en route to group add's fade off, or lull with a good charisma buff to recover on resists initially and proximity pull the least then control what ever else comes along with mez's or allow the chanter to take over ect. You don't have to bring spectacular singles just a controllable flow of mobs. </span></td>
			</tr><tr>
