			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Hard LDoN<a name="45828"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jun 14 04 5:33 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I did my first hard LDoNs as a bard yesterday, and we did 3 on the trot with good success. All 3 were collects and completed within 60 minutes, the first took about 45 mins.
<br />

<br />
I had a charisma buff on, for a total of about 250 cha. I didn't use cha song on top of that but without the buff I probably would have. Lulling was very ineffective; many resists and a few critical ones. In general I would lull with the anticipation that mobs would aggro from the lull, and prepare accordingly. 
<br />

<br />
I found mezz and snare to be really useful tools in combination with fade. Most mobs can be pulled in pairs with careful positioning and ordering of pulls. I'd pull with oos (don't have hos yet) to increase success on mezzing, or sometimes directly with a mezz, let the others come, then fade. 
<br />

<br />
Definitely having more FT helps a lot. A highly recommend spending tribute on FT5 from there if you aren't hitting the cap of FT15 without it. With a solstice earring and composers boots, most people can achieve FT9 quite quickly. Then there's the MC3 AAs, and a few other FT1 items.
<br />

<br />
Also helps to have a good cleric and a good MT that can grab aggro fast. I've only got FM and RS3, and can't take many hits so having an MT who's on the ball really helped.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
